{"questionId":"25966","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time it takes Suzi to drive from home to work each morning is normally distributed with a&nbsp;mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn></math> minutes and a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>σ</mi></math> minutes.</p>\n<p>On <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of days, it takes Suzi longer than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math> minutes to drive to work.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>On a randomly selected day, find the probability that Suzi’s drive to work will take&nbsp;longer than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn></math> minutes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>45</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0886718</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0887</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25966","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"On a randomly selected day, find the probability that Suzi’s drive to work will take longer than 45 minutes.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}